The paper deals with measuring similarity in appearance between different materials, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The use of deep learning architecture and novel loss function suggests a focus on machine learning (MM) and artificial intelligence (AI). The evaluation and applications of the model also suggest a possible connection to machine learning (MM) and computational linguistics (LG).
